- chop shrooms and add to skillet
- add 1/4 cup water
- set burner to 180°C to cook and boil off water, stirring as they cook (should take 4-8 mins)
- once water is mostly gone and temp starts rising, add smol amount of oil
- cook a further 4-8 mins until browned

[ optional, extra flaves *after browning mushrooms* ]
- make space in center of pan
- pan temp to 150°C
- add butter and shallots
- cook down until soft
- add vinegar and mustard, and optionally broth
- cook down again
